1
00:00:01,841 --> 00:00:05,001
我叫乌特雷德，乌特雷德之子
My name is uhtred, son of uhtred.

2
00:00:05,481 --> 00:00:07,921
我生来便是诺森布里亚的郡长
I was born an ealdorman of northumbria.

3
00:00:08,121 --> 00:00:10,521
贝班堡的正统继承人
The rightful heir to bebbanburg.

4
00:00:10,921 --> 00:00:14,281
但命运安排我在丹麦人中长大
But fate decreed I would be raised as a Dane.

5
00:00:17,001 --> 00:00:18,641
那就是我的生活
That was my life

6
00:00:18,841 --> 00:00:21,081
直到我的家人惨遭杀害
until my family was murdered.

7
00:00:27,881 --> 00:00:30,361
外面传言说称我是罪魁祸首
Word was spread that I was to blame.

8
00:00:30,561 --> 00:00:33,881
一个撒克逊奴隶，在婚宴上杀了自己的主人
A Saxon slave, he killed his master at a wedding party.

9
00:00:36,201 --> 00:00:39,321
于是，我和布丽达逃往威塞克斯
And so, with brida, I fled to wessex.

10
00:00:39,521 --> 00:00:42,881
去投奔阿尔弗雷德，他后来成为了国王
To Alfred, a man who would become king.

11
00:00:44,841 --> 00:00:47,801
尽管并非所有人都认可  - 我才是父亲的继承人
Though not all agreed. - I am my father's heir.

12
00:00:48,281 --> 00:00:50,961
我向这位国王宣誓效忠
I swore an oath to this king.

13
00:00:51,481 --> 00:00:53,921
这份誓言让我失去了布丽达，也让我无法
An oath that lost me brida and prevented me

14
00:00:54,121 --> 00:00:55,961
去投奔我的兄弟拉格纳
from joining my brother ragnar.

15
00:00:58,001 --> 00:01:00,881
但命运主宰一切
But destiny is all.

16
00:01:50,761 --> 00:01:52,841
你不配成婚
You don't deserve to marry.

17
00:01:53,921 --> 00:01:57,121
那位女士是名门闺秀，你不过是个异教徒
That woman is a lady and you're a heathen.

18
00:01:57,561 --> 00:02:00,041
你就算泡一整天澡，身上还是臭
You could bathe all day, you'd still stink.

19
00:02:00,401 --> 00:02:05,081
你一直盯着我看，小奥达？难不成你想让我娶你？
Have you been watching me, odda the boy? Should I be marrying you?

20
00:02:05,401 --> 00:02:07,561
给你十枚银币，让你离开这里怎么样
Ten pieces of silver for you to walk away.

21
00:02:08,041 --> 00:02:09,841
你父亲知道你在这儿吗？
Does your father know you're here?

22
00:02:10,401 --> 00:02:11,841
十一枚
Eleven pieces.

23
00:02:17,401 --> 00:02:19,961
不如用我这把剑等重的银子来换？
How about my sword's weight in silver?

24
00:02:20,121 --> 00:02:22,041
胡说八道
Nonsense.

25
00:02:23,841 --> 00:02:27,641
那我就娶那姑娘，今晚我还会和她做爱
Then I'll marry the girl. And tonight, I'll plough her.

26
00:02:29,521 --> 00:02:33,681
- 你为何要这样说她? - 也许你想把她据为己有
- Why must you talk of her like that? - Perhaps you'd like her for yourself.

27
00:02:34,401 --> 00:02:36,681
你自己想占有她, 是不是? 
You want her beneath you. Am I right?

28
00:02:36,841 --> 00:02:38,761
你这人根本没法讲道理
You're impossible to reason with.

29
00:02:38,961 --> 00:02:40,841
什么事在你眼里都是游戏
Everything is a game.

30
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:45,321
看在米尔德丝的份上, 我希望你在这儿待的时间不会太久
I hope for mildrith's sake, your time on this earth is short.

31
00:02:45,761 --> 00:02:47,481
你不是郡长
You are not an ealdorman

32
00:02:47,641 --> 00:02:49,681
永远也当不了
and never shall be.

33
00:02:57,161 --> 00:02:59,601
嘿! 这边! 
Hey! Here!

34
00:03:10,641 --> 00:03:13,561
我没被允许去见她, 我还没见过她
I wasn't allowed to meet her. I haven't seen her.

35
00:03:13,721 --> 00:03:15,321
规矩就是这样
It is the way.

36
00:03:15,481 --> 00:03:19,041
直到昨天我才知道她的存在
I was unaware of her existence till yesterday.

37
00:03:19,481 --> 00:03:22,881
- 她是不是又朴素又虔诚? - 虔诚是肯定的
- She'll be plain and pious? - Oh, she'll be pious, all right.

38
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:26,441
要是她是个荡妇, 阿尔弗雷德早就扑上去了
If she was a leg-spreader, Alfred would have been on her by now.

39
00:03:26,601 --> 00:03:28,281
你见过她? 
Have you seen her?

40
00:03:28,441 --> 00:03:30,201
远远看了一眼
A distance away.

41
00:03:30,521 --> 00:03:32,801
"朴素"这个词倒是贴切
"Plain" is a fair description.

42
00:03:33,401 --> 00:03:34,961
聘礼给了多少? 
How much was the bride price?

43
00:03:35,121 --> 00:03:36,801
三十三枚
Thirty-three pieces.

44
00:03:36,825 --> 00:03:38,825
我得支付给她的教父奥达
Which  I've  paid,  to  her  Godfather  Odda,

45
00:03:39,121 --> 00:03:41,521
我也会确保她收到这笔钱
and which I'll make sure she receives.

46
00:03:43,441 --> 00:03:45,801
我许下过承诺
I've made promises.

47
00:03:46,841 --> 00:03:48,321
复仇之类的
Revenge and such.

48
00:03:48,521 --> 00:03:51,121
你知道你为什么在这里吗? 
Why are you here? Do you know?

49
00:03:51,601 --> 00:03:53,401
她给我带来了土地
She brings land.

50
00:03:53,561 --> 00:03:57,961
我会成为阿尔弗雷德麾下的领主, 能积累财富, 聚拢人马
I'll become a lord under Alfred. I'll be able to make wealth, gather men.

51
00:03:58,201 --> 00:04:01,161
- 夺回属于我的东西    - 这些理由已经足够了
- Take back what's mine. - All reasons enough.

52
00:04:02,481 --> 00:04:04,521
朴素不朴素不重要, 她能派上用场就行
Plain or not, she serves her purpose.

53
00:04:04,721 --> 00:04:07,121
你许下的承诺必须兑现
The promises you have made will stand.

54
00:04:07,441 --> 00:04:09,241
血仇可以追一辈子
Blood feuds last a lifetime.

55
00:04:09,401 --> 00:04:14,201
你要做的, 浑球, 就是一天一天地活下去, 直到最后一天
What you do, arseling, is you keep living each day until the last.

56
00:04:16,921 --> 00:04:21,401
神父终于来了, 咱们赶紧把事儿办了
The priest has arrived finally. Let's get this done.

57
00:04:22,841 --> 00:04:24,761
你不必做这件事
You do not need to "get this done."

58
00:04:24,921 --> 00:04:27,001
我会去向阿尔弗雷德求情
I will make a plea to Alfred.

59
00:04:33,761 --> 00:04:36,161
她来了, 感谢主
She's here, praise god.

60
00:04:36,321 --> 00:04:39,801
你站直了, 看起来正经一点, 哪怕人不是很干净
You should stand and look respectful, if not entirely clean.

61
00:04:39,961 --> 00:04:42,041
- 她看起来怎么样?    - 我猜是吓坏了
- How does she look? - Terrified, I bet.

62
00:04:51,481 --> 00:04:54,401
贝奥卡神父, 能不能把仪式简短一点
If you could be brief with the ceremony, father beocca,

63
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:57,041
我会很感激的, 我还有事要见国王
I'd be grateful. I have business with the king.

64
00:04:58,641 --> 00:05:01,161
新娘已经收到聘礼了吗? 
The bride has been given her price?

65
00:05:01,681 --> 00:05:03,481
她会的
She will.

66
00:05:07,001 --> 00:05:08,841
你来作见证
You are witness.

67
00:05:09,001 --> 00:05:10,641
谢谢你, 大人
Thank you, lord.

68
00:05:11,761 --> 00:05:15,641
若两位新人愿意到祭坛前来... 
If the betrothed couple would like to join me at the altar...

69
00:05:17,601 --> 00:05:20,881
- 双手相握  - 快点
- And join hands. - Be brief.

70
00:05:41,281 --> 00:05:44,521
愿天上的主垂目怜悯
May god in his heaven look down with mercy

71
00:05:44,681 --> 00:05:48,001
他的虔诚仆人乌特雷德与米尔德丝
upon his devoted servants, uhtred and mildrith.

72
00:05:48,161 --> 00:05:51,841
愿主赐福这对夫妇, 以爱、子嗣与财富
May he bless their union with love, and children, and wealth.

73
00:05:52,321 --> 00:05:56,241
也愿他们时刻感恩颂赞
And may they, in turn, be sure to give thanks and praise,

74
00:05:56,401 --> 00:06:00,561
每日依照主的圣言而活, 阿门
and live each day according to his holy word. Amen.

75
00:06:01,121 --> 00:06:03,961
- 阿门  - 阿门
- Amen. - Amen.

76
00:06:04,161 --> 00:06:07,561
你们在天主的见证下，已结为夫妻
You are now joined as man and wife in the eyes of god.

77
00:06:14,081 --> 00:06:15,521
喜悦的泪水
Tears of joy.

78
00:06:33,041 --> 00:06:35,321
让我来帮你
Allow me to help you with that.

79
00:06:37,321 --> 00:06:39,081
谢谢你，大人
Thank you, lord.

80
00:06:41,361 --> 00:06:43,201
我是个幸运的人... 
I'm a lucky man...

81
00:06:44,121 --> 00:06:46,361
能娶到如此美丽的妻子
To have such a beautiful wife.

82
00:06:48,161 --> 00:06:50,441
追求你的人一定不少吧
There must have been many suitors, I'm sure.

83
00:06:50,601 --> 00:06:52,641
你太抬举我了
You're kind to believe so.

84
00:06:52,801 --> 00:06:54,321
我说得对吗? 
Am I right?

85
00:06:55,921 --> 00:06:57,401
没有合适的，大人
None suitable, lord.

86
00:06:57,761 --> 00:07:00,121
我叫乌特雷德，叫我乌特雷德就行
My name's uhtred. Call me uhtred.

87
00:07:00,281 --> 00:07:03,881
浑球，该上路了
Arseling, time we were on our way.

88
00:07:04,481 --> 00:07:07,961
或者，你有时候也可以叫我"浑球" 
Or from time to time, you may wish to call me "arseling."

89
00:07:17,521 --> 00:07:18,961
大人
Lord.

90
00:07:21,361 --> 00:07:22,921
丹麦人
Danes.

91
00:07:24,241 --> 00:07:25,801
我们为什么停下来? 
Why are we stopping?

92
00:07:27,041 --> 00:07:28,761
他们是什么人? 
Who are they?

93
00:07:28,921 --> 00:07:31,121
多半是强盗
Foragers, most likely.

94
00:07:31,641 --> 00:07:34,921
- 但终归是丹麦人       - 他们会动手吗? 
- But Danes all the same. - Will they attack?

95
00:07:35,401 --> 00:07:36,801
继续走
We walk on.

96
00:07:41,841 --> 00:07:43,321
他们跟上来了
They're following us.

97
00:07:43,481 --> 00:07:45,361
继续走，他们不会动手的
We walk on. They won't attack.

98
00:07:47,841 --> 00:07:50,121
那你为什么拔剑了? 
 Then why have you drawn your sword?

99
00:07:50,281 --> 00:07:53,241
让他们知道，至少有一个人会死在这里
To show them at least one of them will die.

100
00:07:54,441 --> 00:07:55,841
一个，或者两个
One or two.

101
00:07:57,241 --> 00:08:01,161
- 强盗们已经深入威塞克斯了   - 那是古思伦的人
- Foragers are deep into wessex. - They're guthrum's men.

102
00:08:01,761 --> 00:08:04,121
他们离伦敦有点远
They're a long way from lundene.

103
00:08:11,561 --> 00:08:14,121
大人, 婚礼已经举行了
Lord, the marriage has taken place.

104
00:08:14,281 --> 00:08:16,641
他们现在正在去农庄的路上
They are now on the road to the farmstead.

105
00:08:16,801 --> 00:08:19,121
好消息, 谢谢你, 奥达
Good news. Thank you, odda.

106
00:08:19,561 --> 00:08:22,121
现在看看他如何应对这个挑战
We shall see how he responds to the challenge.

107
00:08:23,841 --> 00:08:27,401
婚事已成, 大人, 我确实担心米尔德丝
Now it is done, lord, I do fear for mildrith.

108
00:08:27,961 --> 00:08:30,081
她得亲口告诉他实情
She will have to give him the facts.

109
00:08:30,761 --> 00:08:34,601
他肯定要冲她发火, 奥达, 这我明白
Oh, he will bark at her, odda, I'm sure.

110
00:08:34,761 --> 00:08:38,121
但他真正的怒火, 是留给你我的
But his real anger will be reserved for you and I.

111
00:08:38,281 --> 00:08:40,921
他不会甘心受天主与国王双重约束
He will not like being beholden to god and to king.

112
00:08:41,081 --> 00:08:43,481
但若他想成为一个真正的郡长
But if he is to become a true ealdorman,

113
00:08:44,121 --> 00:08:47,041
就必须承担这份重担, 这是对他的考验
he must accept his burden. That is the test.

114
00:08:47,881 --> 00:08:49,201
是, 大人
Yes, lord.

115
00:08:51,321 --> 00:08:55,521
米尔德丝是赐给他的美丽慰藉
Mildrith is his beautiful consolation.

116
00:08:58,921 --> 00:09:01,321
他对她动心了吗? 
Was he struck by her?

117
00:09:03,761 --> 00:09:05,361
动心了, 大人
He was, lord.

118
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:17,041
你怎么还没成家? 
Why are you not already married?

119
00:09:17,841 --> 00:09:21,241
你这年纪, 早该有两三个孩子了
You're old enough to have had two or three children by now.

120
00:09:21,441 --> 00:09:23,161
浑球大人
Lord arseling.

121
00:09:23,361 --> 00:09:26,121
问这话的时机早过了
There is a time for such questions, and it has past.

122
00:09:26,321 --> 00:09:28,881
阿尔弗雷德为何赐我这样一位美丽的新娘? 
Why has Alfred gifted me such a beautiful bride?

123
00:09:33,081 --> 00:09:35,201
我猜是因为欠别人债吧
Has a debt, I'm guessing.

124
00:09:35,361 --> 00:09:37,801
这不是我该说的
It's not my place to tell you.

125
00:09:40,481 --> 00:09:42,081
多少? 
How much?

126
00:09:43,841 --> 00:09:46,721
我父亲想在天主面前得蒙恩宠
My father wanted to find favour with god

127
00:09:46,881 --> 00:09:49,881
所以他把十分之一的土地献给了教会
so he devoted a tenth of his land to the church.

128
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:53,641
教会不拥有这片地, 但有权收取它的出产
They do not own it, but they are entitled to its yield.

129
00:09:53,841 --> 00:09:56,921
实际上他们要求收取出产
Indeed, they demand its yield,

130
00:09:57,081 --> 00:09:59,561
就算庄稼欠收、丹麦人来袭也不例外
even when crops fail and Danes raid.

131
00:09:59,881 --> 00:10:01,241
天主是善的
God is good.

132
00:10:01,401 --> 00:10:03,961
于是主教把我父亲告上了法庭
So the bishop took my father to law.

133
00:10:04,561 --> 00:10:06,001
债务有多少?
How much is the debt?

134
00:10:06,401 --> 00:10:08,241
教会就是法律
The church is the law.

135
00:10:08,401 --> 00:10:11,481
法律裁定我父亲欠了他们一大笔钱
And the law decreed that my father owed to them a huge sum.

136
00:10:11,641 --> 00:10:14,841
- 根本超出了他的还款能力        - 多少钱? 
- Quite beyond his ability to pay. - How much?

137
00:10:15,961 --> 00:10:18,881
他不久后就去世了
He died soon after.

138
00:10:23,041 --> 00:10:25,041
是一笔相当大的数目, 大人
It is a substantial amount, lord.

139
00:10:26,161 --> 00:10:27,601
而且每年都在增加
It increases yearly.

140
00:10:27,761 --> 00:10:30,561
阿尔弗雷德本可以免除这笔债, 但他选择不这么做
Alfred could remove the debt. He has chosen not to.

141
00:10:31,241 --> 00:10:33,681
欠款共计两千先令, 大人
The amount owed is 2,000 shillings, lord.

142
00:10:35,921 --> 00:10:37,681
该死的阿尔弗雷德
Damn him.

143
00:10:39,161 --> 00:10:41,161
他所坚守的一切都该死
Damn everything he stands for.

144
00:10:41,321 --> 00:10:44,881
- 该死的他的教会和他的天主     - 大人, 我不喜欢你说这种亵渎的话
- Damn his church and his god. - Lord, I don't like your blasphemy.

145
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:46,761
我的名字是乌特雷德! 
My name is uhtred!

146
00:10:55,041 --> 00:10:58,681
不过我那么晚才看清这一切，叫我"浑球"也行
Though by all means, call me "arseling" for not seeing this sooner.

147
00:11:14,801 --> 00:11:16,401
你的新家
Your new home.

148
00:11:16,561 --> 00:11:19,441
土地不错, 房子需要修缮
The land is good. The buildings need repair.

149
00:11:19,601 --> 00:11:22,401
住在这片地上的几户人家过来向我们道喜
Families who live on the land come to wish us well.

150
00:11:22,601 --> 00:11:24,401
让他们回自己家去
Send them back to their homes.

151
00:11:25,881 --> 00:11:29,801
他们是来给我们送祝福的, 我认识他们一辈子了
They've come to wish us well. I have known them my whole life.

152
00:11:29,961 --> 00:11:32,401
大人, 夫人
Lord. Lady.

153
00:11:32,561 --> 00:11:35,561
奥斯瓦尔德管着这片农庄, 就住在附近
Oswald manages the farmstead. He lives nearby.

154
00:11:35,761 --> 00:11:39,561
欢迎回家, 也请接受我们对你们婚事的美好祝愿
Welcome home. And may we offer our good wishes on your marriage.

155
00:11:39,721 --> 00:11:41,961
谢谢你, 奥斯瓦尔德, 谢谢你们
Thank you, oswald. Thank you.

156
00:11:42,121 --> 00:11:46,001
你们大家特地聚在这里迎接我和我的主君乌特雷德大人, 真是太好了
And how kind of you all to gather to greet me and my lord uhtred.

157
00:11:46,161 --> 00:11:49,761
大人, 我们已经备好了桌席, 请您享用
We have prepared a table, lord, for your pleasure.

158
00:11:51,401 --> 00:11:53,801
谢谢你们的心意, 不过我们累了
You have my thanks, but we're tired.

159
00:11:53,961 --> 00:11:55,921
明白, 大人
Of course, lord.

160
00:11:58,401 --> 00:12:00,481
谢谢你, 奥斯瓦尔德, 你真好
Thank you, oswald. You're kind.

161
00:12:01,841 --> 00:12:04,641
我为每家准备了一份婚礼礼物
I have a wedding gift for each family.

162
00:12:05,001 --> 00:12:07,401
- 是银子       - 谢谢您, 米尔德丝夫人
- It is silver. - Thank you, lady mildrith.

163
00:12:07,561 --> 00:12:11,001
- 感谢你们的善意与忠诚         - 真的太感谢了
- For your kindness and your loyalty. - Thank you so much.

164
00:12:11,161 --> 00:12:13,441
感谢你们在我不在时替我照看这片土地
For taking care of the land in my absence.

165
00:12:18,641 --> 00:12:21,281
哦, 这景象看着真顺眼
Now, there's a welcome sight.

166
00:12:27,961 --> 00:12:31,561
我本以为这里会有一座大厅, 结果就看到这个
I was expecting there to be a hall, and I find this.

167
00:12:32,801 --> 00:12:35,521
把债还清了, 你就能建大厅
Pay off your debts, and you can build a hall.

168
00:12:36,201 --> 00:12:39,481
我没说错吧, 那混蛋很精明的——阿尔弗雷德
Didn't I tell you the bastard thinks? Alfred.

169
00:12:40,521 --> 00:12:43,921
他要是以为能让我低头求他, 那他想得美
If he believes he can make me beg, he can think again.

170
00:12:45,401 --> 00:12:48,281
他不是要你低头, 他要的是你服从
He doesn't want you to beg. He wants you to obey.

171
00:12:48,641 --> 00:12:50,161
绝无可能
Never.

172
00:12:50,921 --> 00:12:53,361
大人, 如果您不需要我了, 我去歇着了
If you have need for me, lord, I'll be resting.

173
00:12:53,521 --> 00:12:55,401
我确实累了
It seems I am tired.

174
00:12:55,561 --> 00:13:00,161
我欠教会两千先令的债，你倒把银子分给你的佃户
I'm 2,000 shillings in debt to the church, and you hand out silver to your tenants.

175
00:13:00,721 --> 00:13:02,801
那是我的银子
It is my silver.

176
00:13:03,601 --> 00:13:06,881
- 你可以拿走我钱袋里的钱      - 我不要你钱袋里的钱
- Have what's in my purse. - I don't want what's in your purse.

177
00:13:07,081 --> 00:13:08,441
那你为何要骂我? 
Then why scold me?

178
00:13:13,041 --> 00:13:16,241
那个白胖子, 你庄子上的管事
The stoat. Your farmstead master.

179
00:13:16,401 --> 00:13:18,721
- 奥斯瓦尔德   - 得盯紧他
- Oswald. - He'll need to be watched.

180
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:22,041
- 他是我父亲信任的人   - 他活得太滋润了
- He was trusted by my father. - He lives too well.

181
00:13:22,201 --> 00:13:26,401
- 我正要去谷仓     - 你可以睡在屋里
- I'm on my way to the barn. - You can sleep in the house.

182
00:13:27,001 --> 00:13:29,801
我更喜欢谷仓, 谢谢
I prefer the barn. Thank you.

183
00:13:29,961 --> 00:13:31,721
今晚可是你们的新婚之夜
It is your wedding night.

184
00:13:32,241 --> 00:13:33,881
夫人, 晚安
Good night, lady.

185
00:13:34,241 --> 00:13:35,881
浑球
Arseling.

186
00:13:44,361 --> 00:13:46,161
我可以走了吗? 
May I leave now?

187
00:13:46,761 --> 00:13:50,961
你收了多少银子作为聘礼? 
How many pieces of silver did you receive as your price?

188
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:52,881
十八块
Eighteen.

189
00:13:53,241 --> 00:13:55,081
这数目对吗? 
Is that correct?

190
00:13:55,641 --> 00:13:59,561
- 聘礼是三十三块    - 我相信这只是个疏失
- The price was 33. - I'm sure it was an honest mistake.

191
00:14:00,761 --> 00:14:02,601
你被骗了
You were robbed,

192
00:14:02,961 --> 00:14:04,761
就像我也被骗了一样
as I was robbed.

193
00:14:05,281 --> 00:14:08,801
那笔钱是你的保障, 你会拿到全部, 一分不少
That price is your security, and you will have it, all of it.

194
00:14:11,041 --> 00:14:12,521
我可以去歇息了吗? 
May I rest?

195
00:14:18,721 --> 00:14:21,761
大人, 很抱歉今天让您失望了
I'm sorry the day has been a disappointment for you, lord.

196
00:15:19,361 --> 00:15:21,361
你心地很好
You have a good heart.

197
00:15:22,201 --> 00:15:24,481
还把自己的银子送出去
Gifting your silver.

198
00:15:26,761 --> 00:15:30,081
奥达还欠你十五块, 我会让他补上
Odda owes you 15 pieces more. I'll see that he pays.

199
00:15:31,281 --> 00:15:33,761
这笔债务不是你的过错, 我不怪你
And the debt's not something I blame you for.

200
00:15:35,001 --> 00:15:39,001
阿尔弗雷德欺骗了我, 我当初该更谨慎的
It's Alfred's deceit. I should have been wiser.

201
00:15:42,081 --> 00:15:44,121
只是你让我迷了眼
Though I was blinded by you.

202
00:15:53,841 --> 00:15:55,521
你该吃点东西
You should eat.

203
00:15:56,321 --> 00:15:59,641
我也该吃点，但我不想一个人吃
I should eat. But I don't want to eat alone.

204
00:16:02,201 --> 00:16:04,521
天主让我成为你的妻子
God has made me your wife.

205
00:16:04,681 --> 00:16:06,001
这其中必有缘由
There must be a reason.

206
00:16:07,201 --> 00:16:08,561
天主是慈善的
God is good.

207
00:17:07,481 --> 00:17:09,641
你在看什么
What is it you're looking at?

208
00:17:18,681 --> 00:17:20,841
那片土地上有一道伤痕
There's a scar across the land there.

209
00:17:21,401 --> 00:17:25,001
是丹麦人的行军长龙，没有尽头
The never-ending line of Danes on the march.

210
00:17:27,001 --> 00:17:28,521
拉格纳
Ragnar.

211
00:17:32,601 --> 00:17:36,361
等消息传到阿尔弗雷德那里，早就来不及了
By the time word reaches Alfred, it would be too late.

212
00:17:37,041 --> 00:17:39,081
除非他们长了翅膀
They would need wings.

213
00:17:45,801 --> 00:17:49,361
奥斯瓦尔德，那个方向是什么城镇
Oswald, what town lays in that direction?

214
00:17:49,561 --> 00:17:51,641
如果他们继续往西走，一两天后
If they keep going west, in a day or so,

215
00:17:51,801 --> 00:17:54,121
就会到达沃勒姆的要塞
they'll come to the fortress at wareham.

216
00:17:55,201 --> 00:17:59,281
带上你的家人和其他人躲进山里，等他们过去，快去
Take your family and the others to the hills till they've passed. Do it now.

217
00:17:59,481 --> 00:18:02,561
- 米尔德丝夫人呢？ - 她跟我一起走... 
- And the lady mildrith? - She travels with me...

218
00:18:03,241 --> 00:18:04,881
去温彻斯特
To Winchester.

219
00:18:05,721 --> 00:18:07,401
是，大人
Yes, lord.

220
00:18:12,001 --> 00:18:13,921
你看到多少人
How many do you see?

221
00:18:14,121 --> 00:18:16,161
问题是，还会有多少人跟来
The question is, how many will follow?

222
00:18:21,641 --> 00:18:25,961
威塞克斯正在遭到入侵，而我们却被告知等着，等他祈完祷
Wessex is being invaded and we're told to wait while he prays.

223
00:18:26,121 --> 00:18:27,961
天主是他的力量，乌特雷德
God is his strength, uhtred.

224
00:18:28,121 --> 00:18:30,521
他现在该上马冲阵，不是跪在地上祈祷
He needs to be on horseback, not on his knees.

225
00:18:33,321 --> 00:18:36,321
- 我讨厌这个地方   - 越来越糟了
- I hate this place. - It grows worse.

226
00:18:41,561 --> 00:18:43,881
没人告诉我你在这里, 真叫人高兴
I was not told you were here. How pleasing.

227
00:18:44,041 --> 00:18:46,201
- 大人    - 没想到你不是一个人（怀孕了）
- Lord. - And so much of you.

228
00:18:46,681 --> 00:18:48,161
他准备好了吗?
Is he ready?

229
00:18:48,321 --> 00:18:50,601
国王已准备就绪, 贤人会议也是
The king is ready, as is his council.

230
00:19:01,721 --> 00:19:05,321
你眼睁睁看着三百多个丹麦人大摇大摆地穿越威塞克斯
You watched 300 men or more march clean across wessex

231
00:19:05,481 --> 00:19:07,201
却什么都没做? 
and you did nothing?

232
00:19:07,521 --> 00:19:09,201
我来这里了
I'm here.

233
00:19:09,561 --> 00:19:12,001
派个信使来就够了
A messenger could have been sent in your place.

234
00:19:12,161 --> 00:19:14,641
- 一个小孩都行    - 你为何不和这些丹麦人对峙? 
- A boy. - Why did you not confront these Danes?

235
00:19:14,801 --> 00:19:17,601
你手下有兵, 你的职责就是培养战士
You have men. That's your purpose, to create warriors.

236
00:19:17,761 --> 00:19:20,401
我只有二十个士兵和他们的妻子, 大多数还在种地
I've been given 20 men and wives, most work the fields.

237
00:19:20,561 --> 00:19:21,881
和丹麦人作战就是送死，大人
It would've been a slaughter, lord.

238
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:23,537
但你选择了不战
But you chose not to fight.

239
00:19:23,561 --> 00:19:24,881
我们也没法知道结果了
We'll never know.

240
00:19:25,081 --> 00:19:27,801
战士只能死一次, 为何要白白送命? 
A warrior can only die once. Why die in vain?

241
00:19:27,961 --> 00:19:31,081
这些丹麦人是从伦敦或东盎格利亚过来的
The Danes have travelled from either lundene or east anglia.

242
00:19:31,241 --> 00:19:32,721
难道没有人盯着他们? 
Were they not being watched?

243
00:19:32,881 --> 00:19:36,801
我们一直在监视停在泰晤士河上的船, 这是个失误
We have been watching the ships which remain on the tames. A mistake.

244
00:19:36,961 --> 00:19:38,761
沃勒姆一旦被占, 战船就会接踵而来
If wareham is captured, ships will follow.

245
00:19:38,961 --> 00:19:41,201
三百人会变成三千人
Three hundred men will become 3,000.

246
00:19:41,601 --> 00:19:45,841
- 我的建议是立刻出兵    - 国王没有向你讨教
- My advice is we march without delay. - I don't recall the king seeking advice.

247
00:19:46,041 --> 00:19:47,961
你亲眼看到了多少丹麦人?
How many Danes did you witness?

248
00:19:48,561 --> 00:19:51,881
远不止两百, 而且个个都是战士
More than 200 by far. Warriors to a man.

249
00:19:53,041 --> 00:19:55,401
沃勒姆恐怕挡不住他们
Wareham will struggle to hold them back.

250
00:19:55,561 --> 00:19:57,521
和平就此终结
The peace is over.

251
00:19:58,801 --> 00:20:00,921
我们别无选择, 只能率兵前往沃勒姆
We have no choice but to march on wareham

252
00:20:01,081 --> 00:20:03,761
祈求天主保佑我们在城堡陷落前赶到
and pray god we arrive before the fortress falls.

253
00:20:03,921 --> 00:20:06,001
大人, 您认为这是一次大规模入侵?
You believe it is an invasion, lord?

254
00:20:06,201 --> 00:20:09,161
很可能是丹麦大军的先兆, 没错
It could well be the beginning of a great Dane army, yes.

255
00:20:09,801 --> 00:20:12,881
会议到此结束, 威塞克斯各位郡长, 整备兵马
Council is over. Ealdormen of wessex, prepare your men.

256
00:20:13,241 --> 00:20:16,161
贝奥卡神父, 出发前我要做祈祷
Father beocca, I shall pray before we leave.

257
00:20:16,321 --> 00:20:18,081
是, 大人
Yes, my lord.

258
00:20:19,201 --> 00:20:22,761
神父, 我想私下觐见国王
Father, I wish to speak to the king privately.

259
00:20:22,921 --> 00:20:24,321
我去通禀
I will ask,

260
00:20:24,481 --> 00:20:27,361
但要我说, 你还得好好学学规矩
but I note that you are still to learn respect.

261
00:20:30,481 --> 00:20:34,201
奥达郡长, 如果我可以说几句
Ealdorman odda, if I may speak out.

262
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:38,361
你还欠我妻子一半的聘礼
You owe my wife half of her bride-price.

263
00:20:38,561 --> 00:20:41,961
我付了三十三块银子, 她只收到十八块
I paid 33 pieces of silver. She received only 18.

264
00:20:42,121 --> 00:20:44,001
她说这是个无心之失
An honest mistake, she assures me.

265
00:20:48,081 --> 00:20:49,441
是这样吗? 
Is this true?

266
00:20:54,241 --> 00:20:55,881
把钱补上
Pay him.

267
00:20:59,841 --> 00:21:02,041
整备人马, 向沃勒姆进发
Ready the men to march on wareham.

268
00:21:04,881 --> 00:21:07,321
你知道吗, 和米尔德丝做爱很愉快
You should know mildrith is a joy to plough.

269
00:21:08,161 --> 00:21:10,001
你就是个异教徒
You're a heathen.

270
00:21:11,441 --> 00:21:12,921
而你是个处男
And you're a virgin.

271
00:21:13,841 --> 00:21:15,521
我才不是
No, I'm not.

272
00:21:19,841 --> 00:21:21,561
他就是
Yes, he is.

273
00:21:46,041 --> 00:21:48,121
怎么了? 
What is it? Hm?

274
00:21:48,401 --> 00:21:51,081
答应我, 你一定要平安回来
Promise me you will come back safely.

275
00:21:52,001 --> 00:21:53,721
两条胳膊, 两只耳朵, 一个都不少
Two arms, both ears.

276
00:21:53,881 --> 00:21:55,921
答应我
Promise me.

277
00:21:56,961 --> 00:21:58,921
我会尽力的
I‘ll do my best.

278
00:22:00,081 --> 00:22:02,401
但你也得答应我同样的事
But only if you do the same.

279
00:22:02,561 --> 00:22:07,321
如果他们来了, 别躲在教堂或修道院里, 去山上, 去林子里
If they come, don't shelter in a church or nunnery. Go to the hills, the woods.

280
00:22:07,481 --> 00:22:09,201
我会来的
I'll come.

281
00:22:11,921 --> 00:22:13,921
为了你们两个
For both of you.

282
00:22:14,681 --> 00:22:16,201
浑球
Arseling.

283
00:22:16,361 --> 00:22:18,881
亲她一下, 咱们该走了
Kiss her and let's be on our way.

284
00:23:33,361 --> 00:23:36,401
米尔德丝, 亲爱的, 我们一直在找你
Mildrith, my dear, we've been looking for you.

285
00:23:36,561 --> 00:23:40,561
埃尔斯威斯夫人, 见到你真好, 看你这气色, 真是好极了
My lady aelswith. How good to see you, and to see you looking as you do.

286
00:23:40,721 --> 00:23:42,481
这孩子就是不肯老实待着
It refuses to keep still.

287
00:23:42,641 --> 00:23:45,281
- 我这个也一样    - 唉, 咱们受的这罪
- Mine is the same. - Oh, how we suffer.

288
00:23:45,441 --> 00:23:47,521
愿主保佑我们都能平安
I pray we both survive.

289
00:23:47,721 --> 00:23:49,201
愿主保佑我们四个都能平安
I pray we four survive.

290
00:23:49,401 --> 00:23:50,721
天主会说了算的
God will decide.

291
00:23:52,561 --> 00:23:56,041
我好想你, 米尔德丝, 每天都为你祈祷
I've missed you, mildrith, and I prayed for you each day.

292
00:23:56,201 --> 00:23:58,641
- 可怜的孩子  - 可怜什么? 
- Poor thing. - Why poor?

293
00:23:59,201 --> 00:24:02,761
跟那个强塞给你的男人住在一起, 一个异教徒
Living with the man they foisted onto you, the pagan.

294
00:24:03,321 --> 00:24:06,081
还得承受他的那些事
Having to take his seed and the like.

295
00:24:06,241 --> 00:24:09,481
乌特雷德是个好人, 他待我很好
Uhtred is decent. He treats me well.

296
00:24:10,241 --> 00:24:11,641
真的很好
He does.

297
00:24:11,961 --> 00:24:14,641
天主会因你的忠诚而赐福于你
God will bless your loyalty.

298
00:24:14,801 --> 00:24:19,281
但但愿他能很快战死沙场
But with luck, he will fall in battle, and soon.

299
00:24:22,441 --> 00:24:24,321
快告诉我你饿了
Please tell me that you're hungry.

300
00:24:24,481 --> 00:24:27,681
- 我有点饿    - 去厨房找我
- I am a little. - Meet me in the kitchens.

301
00:24:27,881 --> 00:24:30,041
我已经为孕妇备好了一顿饭
I have arranged a meal for the pregnant.

302
00:24:30,201 --> 00:24:31,681
但别急着祷告
But do not rush prayers.

303
00:24:31,881 --> 00:24:34,841
不不, 当然不会, 呵
No. No. Of course not. Heh.

304
00:24:44,921 --> 00:24:49,001
主啊, 他不是你最谦卑虔诚的仆人
Lord, he is not your most humble or devout servant.

305
00:24:49,161 --> 00:24:50,681
但我祈求你能... 
But I pray...

306
00:24:51,561 --> 00:24:53,521
保他平安
Keep him safe.

307
00:24:53,961 --> 00:24:56,001
让他完成你的旨意
Let him do your work.

308
00:24:56,761 --> 00:24:59,081
让他亲眼看见自己的孩子
Let him see his child.

309
00:25:03,401 --> 00:25:06,721
我很高兴今天见到你的妻子
I was pleased to see your lady today, your wife.

310
00:25:07,201 --> 00:25:09,041
而且她怀着孩子
And carrying a child.

311
00:25:10,721 --> 00:25:12,601
这是天主的恩赐
It's god's blessing.

312
00:25:13,441 --> 00:25:15,081
感觉就像昨天的事一样
It seems like only yesterday

313
00:25:15,241 --> 00:25:18,441
我先给你施洗, 取名奥斯伯特, 后来又改名乌特雷德
I was baptising you as osbert, and then again as uhtred.

314
00:25:21,241 --> 00:25:23,801
你想和国王谈什么事? 
What is it you wish to speak about with the king?

315
00:25:23,961 --> 00:25:25,961
那是我和国王之间的事
It's between myself and the king.

316
00:25:26,361 --> 00:25:28,441
他关注着你, 乌特雷德
He's watching you, uhtred.

317
00:25:28,465 --> 00:25:30,465
- 天主？ - 阿尔弗雷德
- God?   - Alfred

318
00:25:31,241 --> 00:25:33,521
看你怎么行事, 以国王的身份评判你
Watching how you behave, judging you as a lord

319
00:25:33,721 --> 00:25:35,521
他没有资格评判我
He has no right to judge.

320
00:25:35,681 --> 00:25:37,441
他是国王
He's a king.

321
00:25:39,201 --> 00:25:42,001
他在婚事上骗了我
He lied to me regarding the marriage.

322
00:25:42,161 --> 00:25:43,961
你说的是那笔债吗? 
Are you referring to the debt?

323
00:25:44,481 --> 00:25:46,881
- 你知道这件事? - 这不是秘密
- You know of it? - It's not a secret.

324
00:25:47,041 --> 00:25:49,561
我劝你表现出你已经接受了
And I urge you to show him you accepted,

325
00:25:49,761 --> 00:25:52,561
尤其是那笔债是欠教会的
especially as it is owed to the church.

326
00:25:54,041 --> 00:25:57,161
你必须保持冷静, 乌特雷德, 要懂得敬重
You must remain calm, uhtred, respectful.

327
00:26:07,401 --> 00:26:08,761
大人
My lord.

328
00:26:08,921 --> 00:26:11,601
- 我请求私下... - 你吃过东西了吗? 
- I requested a private... - Have you eaten?

329
00:26:16,841 --> 00:26:21,721
有时候我很馋肉食... 
There are times when I crave meat...

330
00:26:22,961 --> 00:26:25,361
以及别的东西
And other things.

331
00:26:25,561 --> 00:26:30,761
但我知道那满足感转瞬即逝, 痛苦却会绵延
But I know the gratification would be fleeting, the suffering prolonged,

332
00:26:30,921 --> 00:26:32,321
所以我忍着吃粥
and so I suffer gruel.

333
00:26:32,761 --> 00:26:36,841
不过我夫人不准我叫粥, 非要叫"肉汤" 
Though my wife will not allow it to be called anything other than "broth."

334
00:26:37,601 --> 00:26:40,241
你一定会很高兴得知我的细作带来了消息
You will be happy to learn that my spies have news.

335
00:26:40,681 --> 00:26:43,241
- 来自沃勒姆的? - 来自爱尔兰
- From wareham? - From Ireland.

336
00:26:43,401 --> 00:26:47,201
乌巴的兄弟伊瓦尔在那里被杀了, 本来无关紧要
Ivar, brother of ubba, has been killed there, which would be irrelevant,

337
00:26:47,361 --> 00:26:50,281
但乌巴要亲自为他复仇
but for the fact ubba wishes to avenge him personally.

338
00:26:50,601 --> 00:26:52,361
这是真的? 
This is true?

339
00:26:53,521 --> 00:26:58,681
海那边一个爱尔兰人杀了个丹麦人, 天下就此变局
An irishman across the sea kills a Dane, and the world changes.

340
00:26:59,161 --> 00:27:01,161
这是天主的旨意
The hand of god.

341
00:27:03,881 --> 00:27:06,841
乌巴会这么做吗? 就这么抛下古思伦? 
Is this something ubba would do? Abandon guthrum?

342
00:27:07,041 --> 00:27:11,041
为了替兄弟报仇, 会的, 只要他的巫师那边说得通
To avenge his brother, yes. If guided by his sorcerer's story.

343
00:27:12,561 --> 00:27:14,561
他还有个巫师? 
He has a sorcerer?

344
00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:18,521
这巫师是做什么的? 
And what does this sorcerer do?

345
00:27:18,681 --> 00:27:20,601
施法? 行巫术? 
Cast spells? Perform magic?

346
00:27:20,841 --> 00:27:22,161
他出谋划策, 大人
He advises, lord.

347
00:27:22,321 --> 00:27:24,201
他寻找征兆
He looks for omens.

348
00:27:24,361 --> 00:27:28,041
- 吉兆凶兆都看    - 哦, 简直是无稽之谈
- Signs, good and bad. - Oh, what nonsense.

349
00:27:29,281 --> 00:27:31,841
大人, 奇迹若不是魔法, 又是什么? 
What are miracles, lord, if not magic?

350
00:27:32,041 --> 00:27:34,401
奇迹是天主所为, 非人力所及
Miracles are performed by god, not man.

351
00:27:34,561 --> 00:27:37,001
丹麦人也这么说 他们认为预兆是众神赐予的礼物
Danes say the same. Omens are gifts from gods.

352
00:27:37,161 --> 00:27:38,641
他们错了
And they are mistaken.

353
00:27:39,041 --> 00:27:41,361
是谁示意乌巴去爱尔兰的? 
Who gave the sign for ubba to go to Ireland?

354
00:27:41,521 --> 00:27:44,401
- 是你们的神还是他们的神? - 只有一个神
- The hand of your god or theirs? - There's one god.

355
00:27:44,561 --> 00:27:47,081
那他一定也跟丹麦人说过话
Then he must have spoken to the Danes.

356
00:27:49,361 --> 00:27:50,681
乌巴如今去了爱尔兰
With ubba now in Ireland,

357
00:27:50,841 --> 00:27:54,401
古思伦就得决定他是否要单独迎战了
guthrum must now decide whether he will fight alone.

358
00:27:54,721 --> 00:27:56,721
他不会单独出战的
He won't fight alone.

359
00:27:57,001 --> 00:27:58,721
不是说他赢不了
Not that he couldn't win.

360
00:27:58,921 --> 00:28:01,121
他会怕折损太多手下
He will fear losing too many of his men.

361
00:28:01,321 --> 00:28:02,841
是的, 大人
Yes, lord.

362
00:28:04,121 --> 00:28:06,041
我明白了一件事... 
I am learning...

363
00:28:06,201 --> 00:28:09,641
这些异教徒只顾自身利益
That the heathen cares only for personal gain.

364
00:28:10,041 --> 00:28:12,921
丹麦人绝对受不了我喝的粥
A Dane could never suffer my gruel.

365
00:28:13,081 --> 00:28:15,201
应该是"肉汤", 大人
"Broth," lord.

366
00:28:17,961 --> 00:28:21,841
郡长乌特雷德, 你和米尔德丝过得好吗? 
You are happy, ealdorman uhtred, with mildrith?

367
00:28:22,761 --> 00:28:25,321
很好, 大人, 她是个好妻子
Yes, lord. She's a good wife.

368
00:28:27,121 --> 00:28:31,001
不过要是早知道我得欠两千先令, 我当初绝不会娶她
Though I never would have married her had I known I'd owe 2,000 shillings.

369
00:28:31,161 --> 00:28:32,481
而且每年还在涨
Which increases yearly.

370
00:28:32,641 --> 00:28:34,801
您一句话, 这债就能免了
On your word, the debt can be lifted.

371
00:28:34,961 --> 00:28:37,281
我凭什么让教会少收两千先令? 
Why should I deny the church 2,000 shillings?

372
00:28:37,441 --> 00:28:40,681
- 我根本不知道还有这债   - 这又不是什么秘密
- I wasn't aware I'd owe it. - It is not a secret.

373
00:28:42,161 --> 00:28:45,641
正是牺牲与忏悔, 让我们有别于异教徒
Sacrifice and penance are what separate us from the heathen.

374
00:28:46,401 --> 00:28:49,561
我有我的肉汤, 你有你的债
I have my broth, you have your debt.

375
00:28:51,841 --> 00:28:54,201
威塞克斯需要一支军队, 你同意吗? 
Wessex needs an army, would you agree?

376
00:28:54,921 --> 00:28:59,401
一支常设的强大军队
A permanent and formidable army.

377
00:29:01,441 --> 00:29:03,281
是，大人
Yes, lord.

378
00:29:03,841 --> 00:29:08,961
英格兰一旦真正建立起来，就需要一支更强大的军队
England, when it finally emerges, shall need a greater army.

379
00:29:09,281 --> 00:29:14,361
驻军将达数千之众，全都需要粮饷
Garrisons of many thousands of men, all will need feeding and payment.

380
00:29:14,881 --> 00:29:17,801
我打算让所有地主
It is my intention that all landowners shall contribute

381
00:29:17,961 --> 00:29:21,041
共同承担这支军队及其将领的给养
to the feeding of this army and its commanders.

382
00:29:21,801 --> 00:29:24,721
我还需要将领，乌特雷德
And I will need commanders, uhtred.

383
00:29:25,361 --> 00:29:29,361
像罗马那些伟大统帅一样的人
Men like the great generals of Rome.

384
00:29:31,761 --> 00:29:34,361
把这笔债当作一份馈赠吧
Look upon the debt as a gift.

385
00:29:35,161 --> 00:29:39,201
这是你向威塞克斯和英格兰证明忠心的机会
A means of proving your devotion to wessex and to england.

386
00:29:39,361 --> 00:29:43,881
- 要是当初有人告诉我实情……   - 我看你还戴着那枚护身符
- If I'd been told the truth from... - You still wear the amulet, I see.

387
00:29:44,961 --> 00:29:46,441
为了铭记拉格纳伯爵
To remind me of Earl ragnar.

388
00:29:46,641 --> 00:29:50,481
你为何不陪你妻子去教堂？为何不向天主祈祷？
Why do you not attend church with your wife? Why do you not pray to god?

389
00:29:50,641 --> 00:29:53,801
天主创造了我身边的一切
God created everything that surrounds me.

390
00:29:53,961 --> 00:29:57,721
田野、河流、森林，这片大地就是我的教堂
The fields, rivers, the forests. The land is my church.

391
00:29:57,881 --> 00:30:01,201
我每天都在祈祷，大人……
And I pray each day, lord...

392
00:30:01,441 --> 00:30:03,401
默默地祈祷
In silence.

393
00:30:20,761 --> 00:30:22,201
他是管不住的
He cannot be tamed.

394
00:30:23,001 --> 00:30:25,121
但他是可以信任的
But he can be trusted.

395
00:30:26,801 --> 00:30:29,801
我不会彻底放弃他
I will not abandon him completely.

396
00:30:30,361 --> 00:30:33,841
我想他还有用处
He may have a use, I'm sure.

397
00:30:44,601 --> 00:30:47,521
听好了，沃勒姆已经失守
Hear me now. Wareham has fallen.

398
00:30:47,681 --> 00:30:49,481
我们立刻出兵
We march at once.

399
00:30:49,641 --> 00:30:52,961
每个人都要按国王的命令行事
Every man is to be ready to do as the king asks.

400
00:30:53,121 --> 00:30:56,161
丹麦人已经攻占了那座要塞
The Danes have taken the fortress.

401
00:30:56,321 --> 00:30:58,561
沃勒姆已经陷落 立刻出发
Wareham has fallen. We march at once.

402
00:30:58,721 --> 00:31:02,361
今天结束之前, 我们可能就踩在血水和内脏里了
We could be slipping in blood and entrails before the day is out.

403
00:31:35,561 --> 00:31:38,121
别管他 够所有人分的
Leave him. There's enough for everyone.

404
00:31:46,961 --> 00:31:48,841
古思伦, 他们来了
Guthrum, they're here.

405
00:31:49,721 --> 00:31:51,641
撒克逊大军正在集结
The Saxon army is gathering.

406
00:31:52,121 --> 00:31:54,721
- 是阿尔弗雷德吗? - 是
- Is it Alfred? - Yes.

407
00:31:56,321 --> 00:31:58,441
要塞修缮好了吗, 防守稳固吗? 
Is the fortress repaired and secure?

408
00:31:58,465 --> 00:32:00,465
很稳固
Yes

409
00:32:00,561 --> 00:32:03,041
很好, 他不会进攻
Good. He will not attack.

410
00:32:03,201 --> 00:32:06,721
他不需要进攻, 他知道我们几天之内就会断粮
He doesn't need to. He knows we'll be hungry within days.

411
00:32:06,881 --> 00:32:08,921
- 我们可以去劫掠  - 不行
- We can raid. - No.

412
00:32:09,361 --> 00:32:12,841
他会把周边村子的粮仓清空
He will empty all the grain stores in the surrounding villages.

413
00:32:15,561 --> 00:32:22,041
我发现这些教堂房间出奇地安静祥和
I have found these church rooms to be strangely quiet and peaceful.

414
00:32:22,201 --> 00:32:27,321
大人, 我带着兵马跋山涉水横穿英格兰, 不是来这儿挨饿的
Lord, I didn't march my men halfway across england for them to starve.

415
00:32:28,761 --> 00:32:31,681
- 我去城墙巡查          - 拉格纳, 我们是来打仗的
- I shall be on the ramparts. - We came for war, ragnar.

416
00:32:32,081 --> 00:32:34,401
但乌巴背信弃义
But ubba has reneged.

417
00:32:34,561 --> 00:32:38,321
- 他是去为兄弟报仇     - 但你在这里
- To avenge his brother. - But you are here.

418
00:32:40,081 --> 00:32:43,081
你不该去为你父亲报仇吗? 
Should you not be avenging your father?

419
00:32:44,161 --> 00:32:46,801
- 时机未到     - 是啊
- When the time is right. - Yes.

420
00:32:47,001 --> 00:32:49,801
时机未到
When the time is right.

421
00:32:51,681 --> 00:32:54,961
我们已经迈出了进攻威塞克斯的第一步
We have taken the first steps against wessex.

422
00:32:56,201 --> 00:32:59,081
但乌巴的离开让我们实力大损
But ubba has left us weak.

423
00:32:59,561 --> 00:33:02,401
他把我们所有人都置于险地
He put all of our lives at risk.

424
00:33:02,601 --> 00:33:05,241
所以在乌巴回来之前
So until ubba returns,

425
00:33:05,401 --> 00:33:07,761
我们必须谈和
we have to make peace.

426
00:33:20,161 --> 00:33:22,401
所以如果你在那里的话... 
So if you are there...

427
00:33:22,425 --> 00:33:24,425
罗马的天主
God of Rome

428
00:33:26,081 --> 00:33:27,921
来砍死我啊
Strike me down.

429
00:33:30,481 --> 00:33:32,561
我想也不会
I thought not.

430
00:33:34,921 --> 00:33:37,081
我们来这里, 是要让他们看清楚我们有多少人
We are here to show them how many we are.

431
00:33:37,761 --> 00:33:41,521
我们来这里, 是要让他们看清楚我们有多少人! 
We are here to show them how many we are!

432
00:33:41,721 --> 00:33:43,841
我们有天主同在
That we are here with god.

433
00:33:44,001 --> 00:33:45,521
这片土地是我们的
And that this is our land.

434
00:33:45,681 --> 00:33:47,881
我们有天主同在! 
That we are here with god!

435
00:33:48,161 --> 00:33:49,881
这片土地是我们的! 
And this is our land!

436
00:33:51,081 --> 00:33:52,921
这是我们的土地! 
This is our land!

437
00:33:53,121 --> 00:33:55,281
我们的威塞克斯! 
Our wessex!

438
00:33:55,881 --> 00:33:57,641
这是我们的英格兰! 
This is our england!

439
00:33:59,081 --> 00:34:03,881
任何敢来抢夺的异教徒杂种, 我们都要杀光他们! 
And we shall murder any heathen bastard that tries to take it!

440
00:34:24,481 --> 00:34:27,961
- 他们想谈判, 大人     - 我知道他们想要什么
- They wish to talk, lord. - I know what they want.

441
00:34:28,121 --> 00:34:29,521
他们想拖时间
They want time.

442
00:34:30,041 --> 00:34:33,561
奥达, 带上你的卫兵跟我去, 利奥弗里克, 你也来
Odda, with your guards, you shall go with me. Leofric, you as well.

443
00:34:34,161 --> 00:34:37,241
- 还有塞尔比克斯神父   - 是, 大人
- And father selbix. - Yes, lord.

444
00:34:37,441 --> 00:34:39,441
利奥弗里克，你觉得那座要塞怎么样? 
Leofric, What do you make of the fortress?

445
00:34:39,641 --> 00:34:41,921
看起来相当坚固, 大人
It looks strong enough, lord.

446
00:34:42,641 --> 00:34:46,121
没有缺口, 也没有明显损毁
No breach. No signs of lasting damage.

447
00:34:46,281 --> 00:34:48,161
如果我们强攻呢? 
And if we attacked?

448
00:34:49,321 --> 00:34:51,241
我们会损失惨重
We would suffer.

449
00:34:52,241 --> 00:34:55,001
能打进去就算走运了, 大人
We'd be lucky to see the inside, lord.

450
00:34:56,841 --> 00:34:58,521
早上好, 阿尔弗雷德国王
Good morning, king Alfred.

451
00:34:58,721 --> 00:35:00,801
丹麦人古思伦
Guthrum of the Danes.

452
00:35:00,961 --> 00:35:04,441
我现在也是国王了, 东盎格利亚之王
I, too, am a king now, of east anglia.

453
00:35:04,601 --> 00:35:06,001
不必行礼
You don't need to bow.

454
00:35:07,521 --> 00:35:09,081
我来开门见山
I will begin.

455
00:35:09,241 --> 00:35:10,841
我提议停战
I propose a truce.

456
00:35:12,601 --> 00:35:16,441
古思伦伯爵, 要想停战, 你必须再次离开威塞克斯
For any truce to occur, Earl guthrum, you must leave wessex once again.

457
00:35:16,601 --> 00:35:18,961
- 若我拒绝呢? - 我们便将你团团围困
- And if I refuse? - We surround you.

458
00:35:19,121 --> 00:35:20,961
是啊, 你们围住的不过是一座小堡垒
Yes, you surround a small fortress,

459
00:35:21,121 --> 00:35:24,201
但我们丹麦人围住的是你整个王国, 话虽如此
but we Danes surround your entire kingdom. That said,

460
00:35:24,361 --> 00:35:27,441
我已决定从海路撤离
I've decided I shall leave by sea.

461
00:35:28,041 --> 00:35:29,801
因此我要派人去调船
Therefore, I will send for ships.

462
00:35:30,041 --> 00:35:32,401
- 要多少船? - 不超过十五艘
- How many ships? - No more than 15.

463
00:35:33,321 --> 00:35:34,641
好吧
Very well.

464
00:35:34,801 --> 00:35:36,721
你的船有一个月时间抵达
Your ships have one month to arrive.

465
00:35:36,881 --> 00:35:40,441
- 时间不够    - 只供应一个月的食物和麦酒
- Not enough time. - Food and ale for one month only,

466
00:35:40,601 --> 00:35:42,841
否则你就走路滚回东盎格利亚
or you will walk back to east anglia.

467
00:35:43,001 --> 00:35:46,521
那我就调两百艘船来, 希望在我们饿死之前能到
Then I'll send for 200 ships and hope they arrive before we starve.

468
00:35:46,721 --> 00:35:49,441
- 一个月根本不够      - 这是我的底线
- One month is not enough. - That is my limit.

469
00:35:49,641 --> 00:35:52,281
你夺不回这座堡垒, 你心里清楚
You cannot take back the fortress. You know this.

470
00:35:52,441 --> 00:35:54,841
食物和麦酒只供应一个月, 不会再多了
Food and ale for one month, no more.

471
00:35:55,041 --> 00:35:58,241
到那时候, 海上的风暴也该来了
By which time, the sea storms will have arrived.

472
00:35:58,441 --> 00:36:02,441
- 那是主赐的风暴    - 我们会在一个月内离开
- God's storms. - We will be gone within a month,

473
00:36:02,881 --> 00:36:05,681
从食物和麦酒送达之日起算
beginning upon the delivery of food and ale.

474
00:36:16,361 --> 00:36:19,561
乌特雷德, 祈祷结束后来见我
Uhtred, you will come to me following prayers.

475
00:36:19,721 --> 00:36:22,881
- 是, 大人
- 塞尔比克斯神父, 你陪我一同祈祷
- Yes, lord. - Father selbix, you will pray with me.

476
00:36:23,041 --> 00:36:24,801
是, 大人
Yes, lord.

477
00:36:28,921 --> 00:36:30,761
请坐
Please sit.

478
00:36:34,641 --> 00:36:36,281
多谢, 大人
Thank you, lord.

479
00:36:38,681 --> 00:36:41,641
我有件事要交给你, 神父
I have a task for you, father.

480
00:36:42,241 --> 00:36:44,721
大人请说
You only have to speak it.

481
00:36:45,521 --> 00:36:49,801
作为和平的保证, 你将被送去做人质, 一共十人
As a guarantee of the peace, you will be given up as a hostage, one of ten.

482
00:36:50,201 --> 00:36:53,761
丹麦人那边也会交出十人作为交换
The Danes, too, will give ten in exchange.

483
00:36:56,321 --> 00:37:01,401
大人, 异教徒不把神父当回事
Lord, the pagans do not value priests.

484
00:37:01,561 --> 00:37:03,881
你还不如送头猎犬过去呢
You might just as well offer a hound.

485
00:37:04,081 --> 00:37:06,321
我听说古思伦对我们的信仰颇感好奇
I hear guthrum is curious about our faith.

486
00:37:06,481 --> 00:37:09,241
我希望你去做他的老师
I would like you to become his teacher.

487
00:37:10,081 --> 00:37:12,201
给他传道授业
Provide instruction.

488
00:37:13,441 --> 00:37:16,841
要是他不愿意学呢? 
And if he refuses to be a student?

489
00:37:17,561 --> 00:37:19,001
那就坚持下去
Then persist.

490
00:37:19,161 --> 00:37:23,081
用你一贯的方式, 温和, 带点幽默
Gently with humour, as is your manner.

491
00:37:25,001 --> 00:37:26,401
你要清楚... 
Make no mistake...

492
00:37:28,041 --> 00:37:32,401
只要古思伦愿意受洗
Should guthrum ever consent to being baptised,

493
00:37:32,681 --> 00:37:34,881
这场战争就结束了
then this war is over.

494
00:37:35,041 --> 00:37:37,241
英格兰就是我们的了
England is ours.

495
00:37:40,081 --> 00:37:42,961
你做的将是真正的天主的事业
This would be truly god's work you do.

496
00:37:44,641 --> 00:37:46,641
恕我直言, 大人
Forgive me, lord,

497
00:37:47,041 --> 00:37:49,921
我心里确实害怕
but I cannot help but feel afraid.

498
00:37:50,961 --> 00:37:54,321
他们对待神父可不只是杀了了事
They are not content to simply kill a priest.

499
00:37:55,681 --> 00:37:59,001
恐惧人人都有
Fear is within all of us.

500
00:38:00,481 --> 00:38:02,561
勇气也是
As is strength.

501
00:38:32,321 --> 00:38:35,761
大人, 等休战破裂, 我上阵杀敌还更有用
Lord, I'd be more useful as a warrior for when the truce fails.

502
00:38:35,921 --> 00:38:38,121
休战还能撑一段时间
Oh, the truce will hold for a time.

503
00:38:38,281 --> 00:38:41,881
在此期间, 你将是我安插在那座堡垒里的眼线
And in that time, you will be my eyes and ears inside the fortress.

504
00:38:42,041 --> 00:38:44,481
- 监听什么? - 乌巴的消息
- Listening for what? - For ubba.

505
00:38:44,641 --> 00:38:48,081
一旦听说他回来, 你就想办法逃出来
If and when you hear of his return, you will escape.

506
00:38:48,241 --> 00:38:50,721
- 要是我被锁链拴着呢? - 我们的人会解散
- And if I'm in chains? - Our men shall disband.

507
00:38:50,881 --> 00:38:52,201
让他们去种地
There are fields to work.

508
00:38:52,361 --> 00:38:55,841
我会在山丘上建一座烽火台, 你逃出来就点火
I'll build a beacon on the hill. You'll escape and light the fire.

509
00:38:56,041 --> 00:38:58,961
大人, 您知道逃跑几乎是不可能的
Lord, you know that escape will be near impossible.

510
00:38:59,121 --> 00:39:03,561
乌巴一旦回来, 人质就会被杀, 丹麦人随即会发动进攻
If ubba returns, the hostages will be killed and the Danes will attack.

511
00:39:03,721 --> 00:39:05,641
一看到烽火燃起
Upon sight of this beacon being lit,

512
00:39:05,801 --> 00:39:08,601
其他烽火也会相继点燃, 威塞克斯全境都会集结备战
other fires will start. Wessex will be called to arms.

513
00:39:08,761 --> 00:39:12,521
- 如果我拒绝去做人质呢? - 会有另一个人去点那把火
- If I refuse to become a hostage? - Another man shall light the beacon.

514
00:39:12,681 --> 00:39:14,321
你为何就是不肯接纳我? 
Why can't you accept me?

515
00:39:14,481 --> 00:39:17,921
我从未说过半句谎话, 为何总要考验我? 
I've been nothing but truthful. Why am I always put to the test?

516
00:39:18,081 --> 00:39:20,681
你为何不给你的国王应有的尊重? 
Why do you not show your king respect that is due?

517
00:39:20,841 --> 00:39:22,521
因为你, 不管什么地方来的乌特雷德
Because you, uhtred of wherever,

518
00:39:22,681 --> 00:39:26,521
根本没把我当你的国王, 也没把我的天主当你的天主
you do not see me as your king. You do not see my god as your god.

519
00:39:26,681 --> 00:39:28,961
- 大人? - 我还没说完
- My lord? - I am not finished with you yet.

520
00:39:31,841 --> 00:39:34,801
古思伦一直在等乌巴从爱尔兰回来的消息
Guthrum is waiting to hear of ubba's return from Ireland.

521
00:39:34,961 --> 00:39:39,481
我需要尽早得知此事, 越快越好, 而你... 
I need to know when this occurs, sooner rather than later. You...

522
00:39:40,201 --> 00:39:44,841
是唯一有可能最先带回这个消息的人
Are the only man who could possibly provide this information sooner.

523
00:39:45,441 --> 00:39:47,601
没错, 你可能会死
Yes, it is possible that you will die,

524
00:39:47,801 --> 00:39:51,521
但我们大概都难逃一死
but it is likely that we shall all die.

525
00:39:53,281 --> 00:39:55,601
你要去丹麦人那里
You will go to the Danes.

526
00:39:55,881 --> 00:39:57,841
以什么身份去, 是撒克逊人质
How you go, as a Saxon hostage

527
00:39:58,001 --> 00:40:00,761
还是维京勇士, 是你的选择
or as a viking warrior, becomes your choice.

528
00:40:06,601 --> 00:40:08,561
我会照你说的做
I'll do as you ask.

529
00:40:11,601 --> 00:40:15,521
但如果我被扣押期间孩子降生，我请求你给我带个信
But if my child is born while I'm captive, I ask that you send word.

530
00:40:15,721 --> 00:40:17,281
当然
Of course.

531
00:40:17,681 --> 00:40:22,081
若你死在被扣押期间，放心，你的债也随你一起消了
And should you die as a captive, rest assured, your debt shall die with you.

532
00:40:35,921 --> 00:40:37,801
他们会善待我们吗？
Will they treat us well?

533
00:40:37,961 --> 00:40:39,881
你是他们中的一员
You are one of them.

534
00:40:40,881 --> 00:40:43,721
我若是他们的一员，为何还要做人质？
If I am one of them, then why am I a hostage?

535
00:40:44,521 --> 00:40:47,481
只要停战协议还在，他们就会善待我们
They'll treat us well for as long as the truce holds.

536
00:40:47,641 --> 00:40:50,161
- 若协议破裂呢？- 他们会把我们全杀了，
- If it fails? - They'll kill us all,

537
00:40:50,361 --> 00:40:52,601
从神父开始，哈！
starting with the priest. Heh!

538
00:40:53,881 --> 00:40:56,481
我已坦然接受，我已准备好了
I've made my peace. I am ready.

539
00:40:56,841 --> 00:40:59,921
晚上好，愿主保佑你们
Good evening and god bless you all.

540
00:41:00,881 --> 00:41:02,361
可怜的人
Poor wretches.

541
00:41:02,561 --> 00:41:04,201
那我们呢，神父，我们又算什么？
And us, father, what are we?

542
00:41:04,361 --> 00:41:06,761
我们是有福之人，大人，我们认识天主
We are fortunate, lord. We know god.

543
00:41:07,201 --> 00:41:10,281
不过坦白说，我不急着去见他
Although granted, I'm in no hurry to meet him.

544
00:41:10,441 --> 00:41:12,521
愿天主也这么想
Let us pray he feels the same.

545
00:41:12,681 --> 00:41:14,321
阿门
Amen.

546
00:41:39,641 --> 00:41:43,121
就这群乌合之众，还让那么多人胆寒？
Is this rabble what so many are afraid of?

547
00:41:43,281 --> 00:41:45,961
来来来，他们跟孩子没两样
Come. They're like children.

548
00:41:50,721 --> 00:41:53,681
够了，够了！
Enough. Enough!

549
00:41:55,201 --> 00:41:57,521
他们暂时是我们的客人
They are our guests for a while.

550
00:41:58,161 --> 00:42:00,361
只有一条规矩
There's one rule only.

551
00:42:01,281 --> 00:42:03,081
天黑之后，
At nightfall,

552
00:42:03,241 --> 00:42:05,961
所有人集合，到教堂里睡觉
you will gather and sleep at the church.

553
00:42:06,121 --> 00:42:08,201
门会被封死
The doors will be barred.

554
00:42:08,881 --> 00:42:15,081
天亮之后, 你们可以自由行走、交谈、跳跃、交欢、携带武器
At daybreak, you will then be free to walk, talk, jump, hump, carry weapons.

555
00:42:15,481 --> 00:42:18,561
我的人奉命不会杀你们... 
My men have orders not to kill you...

556
00:42:19,561 --> 00:42:22,441
除非你们该死
Unless you deserve to be killed.

557
00:42:26,641 --> 00:42:28,241
我是古思伦
I am guthrum.

558
00:42:28,401 --> 00:42:31,201
总有一天, 我将成为你们的国王
And one day, I shall be your king.

559
00:42:31,401 --> 00:42:33,601
你们听懂我说的了吗? 
Do you understand what I have said?

560
00:42:33,801 --> 00:42:35,521
你们都要说:"是的, 大人" 
You will all say, "yes, lord."

561
00:42:37,321 --> 00:42:39,081
是的, 大人
Yes, lord.

562
00:42:39,241 --> 00:42:41,201
我没听见
I did not hear you.

563
00:42:46,521 --> 00:42:48,281
我们听懂了, 大人
I understand you, lord.

564
00:42:49,161 --> 00:42:51,441
也许我会把你作为礼物送给乌巴
Maybe I will make a present of you to ubba.

565
00:42:51,641 --> 00:42:55,561
- 要是他从爱尔兰回来的话       - 他可能不会回来, 也说不定
- Should he ever return from Ireland. - He may not. That's possible.

566
00:42:55,761 --> 00:42:58,121
但到那时他的人就会成为我的人
But then his men will become my men,

567
00:42:58,281 --> 00:43:01,641
我会亲手杀了你, 以此向他致敬
and I will honour him by killing you myself.

568
00:43:03,281 --> 00:43:05,601
也许用箭
With arrows, perhaps.

569
00:43:05,761 --> 00:43:08,201
- 拉格纳·拉格纳森    - 在这
- Ragnar ragnarson. - Here.

570
00:43:08,361 --> 00:43:11,201
你对这人很熟, 让他别出现在我眼前
You know this one well. Keep him out of my sight.

571
00:43:11,361 --> 00:43:14,281
把他们带去教堂, 给他们吃的
Take them to the church. Feed them.

572
00:43:21,561 --> 00:43:23,721
现在你们到了该待的地方
Now you are where you belong.

573
00:43:24,241 --> 00:43:25,681
现在我和我兄弟在一起了
Now I'm with my brother.

574
00:43:25,841 --> 00:43:30,081
我会让你重新感受身为丹麦人是什么滋味, 让你留下来
I will remind you what it is like to be a Dane and make you stay.

575
00:43:30,841 --> 00:43:32,761
布丽达也在这里
Brida's here.

576
00:43:51,161 --> 00:43:53,881
我梦到过你, 小狐狸
I dream about you, Vixen.

577
00:43:55,441 --> 00:43:57,721
听到这话我一点都不意外
I'm not surprised to hear it.

578
00:43:58,801 --> 00:44:00,681
你长大了, 哈哈
You've grown up. Heh, heh.

579
00:44:04,641 --> 00:44:07,961
你该知道我现在跟着拉格纳, 他是我的男人
You should know I'm with ragnar now. He's my man.

580
00:44:09,281 --> 00:44:10,921
这是好事
That's good.

581
00:44:12,441 --> 00:44:14,001
这是好事
That's good.

582
00:44:15,921 --> 00:44:18,161
你也该知道, 我成婚了
You should know that I am married.

583
00:44:19,281 --> 00:44:20,801
成婚了? 
Married?

584
00:44:22,241 --> 00:44:24,641
- 你真的长大了  - 他成婚了? 
- You have grown up. - He's married?

585
00:44:25,241 --> 00:44:27,121
对, 他成婚了
Yes, he is married.

586
00:44:27,481 --> 00:44:29,681
时间过得比我想的快多了
Time is moving quicker than I thought.

587
00:44:30,201 --> 00:44:31,881
今晚, 我们喝个痛快
Tonight, we get drunk.

588
00:44:32,401 --> 00:44:33,921
必须的
We must.

589
00:44:34,281 --> 00:44:38,321
- 晚上我得呆在教堂里
- 不, 今晚我们喝个痛快
- I need to be inside the church. - No, tonight we get drunk.

590
00:44:38,481 --> 00:44:40,361
我亲自带你去教堂
I'll take you to the church myself.

591
00:44:40,521 --> 00:44:43,681
或者喝倒在哪儿就睡哪儿, 哈哈
Or we sleep where we fall, ha, ha.

592
00:44:44,041 --> 00:44:45,761
还有, 呃... 
And, uh...

593
00:44:46,241 --> 00:44:48,481
我们得谈谈将来的事
We must talk of the future.

594
00:45:02,601 --> 00:45:05,361
我们是桨手! 
We are oarsmen!

595
00:45:08,201 --> 00:45:11,081
乌特雷德, 给我划! 啊! 
Uhtred, pull for me. Aah!

596
00:45:11,241 --> 00:45:15,241
- 我去撒泡尿, 马上回来  - 他会回来的
- I need to piss. I'll return. - He'll return.

597
00:45:15,681 --> 00:45:18,241
拉格纳? 拉格纳? 
Ragnar? Ragnar?

598
00:45:31,441 --> 00:45:34,481
我很久没这么开心地笑过了
I haven't laughed so much in a long time.

599
00:45:34,641 --> 00:45:36,481
那说明你活得不够痛快
Then you haven't been living.

600
00:45:36,641 --> 00:45:40,001
或者像拉文说的, "明日我们便死"
Or as ravn would say, "tomorrow we die."

601
00:45:40,201 --> 00:45:42,161
他什么时候说过这话? 
When did he ever say that?

602
00:45:42,321 --> 00:45:45,201
你去劈柴的时候
When you were out chopping wood.

603
00:45:48,561 --> 00:45:52,961
我是真的要去撒尿
Well, I actually do need to piss.

604
00:45:53,121 --> 00:45:56,321
哈哈, 你该做的是少喝点酒
Ha, ha, what you need to do is to stop drinking.

605
00:45:56,601 --> 00:45:58,681
明天我们就要死了
Tomorrow we die.

606
00:46:05,641 --> 00:46:07,881
- 他很高兴见到你   - 我也想他了
- He's happy to see you. - I've missed him.

607
00:46:11,841 --> 00:46:13,601
我想念你们俩
I miss you both.

608
00:46:21,721 --> 00:46:23,761
她是你的妻子? 
Are you his wife?

609
00:46:24,241 --> 00:46:25,921
我跟他在一起
I'm with him.

610
00:46:27,441 --> 00:46:29,561
- 她漂亮吗? - 嗯
- Is she beautiful? - Mm.

611
00:46:30,161 --> 00:46:33,521
她叫米尔德丝, 很漂亮
Her name's mildrith. Yes, she is beautiful.

612
00:46:37,241 --> 00:46:39,441
她怀了我的孩子
She carries my child.

613
00:46:44,641 --> 00:46:46,841
是谁决定你们成婚的? 
Who decided you should marry?

614
00:46:48,321 --> 00:46:49,641
阿尔弗雷德
Alfred.

615
00:46:52,841 --> 00:46:55,361
我在威塞克斯得到了我想要的那片土地
I have the land I asked for in wessex.

616
00:46:59,401 --> 00:47:01,361
你向阿尔弗雷德宣誓效忠
You swear an oath to Alfred.

617
00:47:01,521 --> 00:47:05,241
你为阿尔弗雷德娶妻, 土地也是阿尔弗雷德赐给你的
You marry for Alfred. You have land given to you by Alfred.

618
00:47:05,441 --> 00:47:07,241
你的妻子怀了你的骨肉
Your wife carries your child.

619
00:47:07,401 --> 00:47:11,001
可阿尔弗雷德竟然把你当人质献出去? 
And yet you're given up as a hostage by Alfred?

620
00:47:11,521 --> 00:47:13,721
你是探子吗, 乌特雷德? 
Are you a spy, uhtred?

621
00:47:17,361 --> 00:47:20,241
一旦乌巴回来的风声传出, 我就得设法逃脱
At the first sign of ubba returning, I am to escape.

622
00:47:22,281 --> 00:47:26,201
但我心里清楚, 乌巴一回来, 那些人质就会被杀
But I know that when ubba returns, the hostages will be killed.

623
00:47:27,281 --> 00:47:29,401
阿尔弗雷德不喜欢我
Alfred's not fond of me.

624
00:47:29,601 --> 00:47:31,321
拒绝他
Refuse him.

625
00:47:32,201 --> 00:47:34,121
拒绝当人质, 加入我们
Refuse to be a hostage. Join us.

626
00:47:36,801 --> 00:47:39,281
我该问你的, 乌特雷德
I should ask you, uhtred.

627
00:47:39,441 --> 00:47:42,641
不是说结果会有什么不同, 但我该问你的
Not that it matters, but I should ask.

628
00:47:42,841 --> 00:47:45,801
布丽达现在跟我在一起, 你有意见吗? 
Is it a problem to you that brida's with me now?

629
00:47:47,721 --> 00:47:50,841
哈, 没有, 我很高兴
Ha, ha, no. I'm happy about it.

630
00:47:52,161 --> 00:47:53,961
- 我发誓  - 好吧
- I swear. - All right.

631
00:47:54,121 --> 00:47:56,681
再说她也不在乎你怎么想
Not that she cares what you think.

632
00:47:56,841 --> 00:47:59,241
反正不管你同不同意我也会睡她, 不过... 
I would hump her regardless. But...

633
00:47:59,441 --> 00:48:01,441
是带着...带着情意的
With... with affection.

634
00:48:01,641 --> 00:48:04,401
- 也是经过我允许的     - 我知道
- And with my permission. - I know.

635
00:48:06,841 --> 00:48:09,001
你知道乌特雷德快当父亲了吗? 
Do you know uhtred's to be a father?

636
00:48:13,801 --> 00:48:16,841
- 什么时候? - 听说快了
- When? - Soon, I'm told.

637
00:48:18,081 --> 00:48:20,001
你想去看孩子出生? 
You would want to see it?

638
00:48:20,881 --> 00:48:24,721
想, 我希望能回去陪我的妻儿
Yes. I hope to return to my wife and child.

639
00:48:27,441 --> 00:48:29,081
拉格纳
Ragnar.

640
00:48:29,441 --> 00:48:34,041
我会和你一起为父亲报仇, 基尔坦会付出代价的
I'll be with you to avenge our father. Kjartan will pay.

641
00:48:34,241 --> 00:48:36,961
你几个月前就该带着布丽达来找我了
You should have joined me months ago with brida.

642
00:48:37,121 --> 00:48:38,841
我宣过誓
I'd sworn an oath.

643
00:48:39,041 --> 00:48:41,361
对一个烂透了的撒克逊王
To a poxy Saxon king.

644
00:48:41,521 --> 00:48:44,281
乌巴要我的命, 我无处可去
Ubba wanted me dead. There was nowhere else to go.

645
00:48:44,441 --> 00:48:46,761
我一直在想那天晚上在林子里的事
I've thought about that night in the woods.

646
00:48:46,921 --> 00:48:50,801
- 你当时可以选择做撒克逊人还是丹麦人  - 不, 我已经宣过誓了
- You had a choice to be Saxon or Dane. - No, I had sworn an oath.

647
00:48:52,041 --> 00:48:54,241
你本该来找我的
You should have joined me.

648
00:48:54,921 --> 00:48:57,641
我会和你一起去杀基尔坦
I'll be with you to kill kjartan.

649
00:49:00,601 --> 00:49:05,481
我带你去教堂, 送你上床休息
I will take you to the church, to your bed.

650
00:49:33,081 --> 00:49:35,361
- 怎么了? - 是个儿子, 夫人
- What is it? - It's a son, lady.

651
00:49:35,521 --> 00:49:37,721
漂亮的小子
A handsome boy.

652
00:49:43,001 --> 00:49:46,241
你将是乌特雷德, 乌特雷德之子
You will be uhtred, son of uhtred.

653
00:49:54,961 --> 00:49:57,001
早安，乌特雷德
Good morning, uhtred.

654
00:49:58,041 --> 00:49:59,921
早安，神父
Good morning, father.

655
00:50:00,561 --> 00:50:02,561
又下雨了
Raining again.

656
00:50:02,961 --> 00:50:05,081
每天都一个样
One day seems like the next.

657
00:50:06,361 --> 00:50:08,081
是啊
It does.

658
00:50:09,441 --> 00:50:12,641
不过至少我们还活着，还能感受这雨
Still, at least we're alive to feel it.

659
00:50:14,041 --> 00:50:16,121
你跟古思伦谈得怎么样?
How are your conversations with guthrum?

660
00:50:16,921 --> 00:50:18,561
他信天主了吗? 
Is he a Christian yet?

661
00:50:18,721 --> 00:50:21,801
我相信时机快到了，真的
I believe the time is near, I do.

662
00:50:21,961 --> 00:50:26,041
我常常让他一个人在教堂里静思
I often leave him to contemplate alone in church.

663
00:50:26,201 --> 00:50:30,321
古思伦喜欢沉思的是战争和王国
Guthrum likes to contemplate war and kingdoms.

664
00:50:30,521 --> 00:50:33,161
天国的荣光也等着他来分享
The kingdom of heaven is his to share.

665
00:50:33,881 --> 00:50:35,521
我已经告诉他了
I've told him.

666
00:50:37,041 --> 00:50:38,841
一个人是可以改变的，乌特雷德
A man can change, uhtred.

667
00:50:42,921 --> 00:50:44,801
前行吧，愿主赐福于你
Onward. God bless you.

668
00:50:45,281 --> 00:50:46,841
祝你度过美好的一天
May you enjoy a good day.

669
00:50:47,001 --> 00:50:48,801
多谢，神父
Thank you, father.

670
00:50:49,761 --> 00:50:53,321
祂是万王之王
He is the king of kings.

671
00:50:53,601 --> 00:50:56,281
能够成就无比伟大的事
Capable of great, great things.

672
00:50:56,441 --> 00:50:58,121
比如什么? 
Such as what?

673
00:50:58,761 --> 00:51:00,801
比如奇迹
Such as miracles.

674
00:51:01,401 --> 00:51:03,081
奇迹? 
Miracles?

675
00:51:03,401 --> 00:51:05,161
比如什么? 
Such as what?

676
00:51:05,681 --> 00:51:09,921
比如您，大人
Such as you, lord.

677
00:51:10,601 --> 00:51:12,841
您就是一个奇迹
You are a miracle.

678
00:51:14,281 --> 00:51:18,361
祂让你刚强而不失仁慈
He has made you strong yet merciful.

679
00:51:18,921 --> 00:51:20,841
祂... 
He has...

680
00:51:21,601 --> 00:51:24,601
让你自豪而不失谦逊
Made you proud yet humble.

681
00:51:25,561 --> 00:51:27,801
祂让你渴望学习
He has made you eager to learn.

682
00:51:29,201 --> 00:51:31,281
祂赐给你自由意志
He has given you free will,

683
00:51:31,441 --> 00:51:36,161
希望你能鼓起勇气, 将祂置于一切之上
hoping that you will find the courage to choose him above all else.

684
00:51:36,521 --> 00:51:40,281
我相信, 我真心相信
And I believe, I truly believe,

685
00:51:40,441 --> 00:51:42,601
祂会得到回报
he will be rewarded.

686
00:51:49,201 --> 00:51:52,441
- 我有消息要带给古思伦    - 他在教堂里
- I have a message for guthrum. - He's in the church.

687
00:52:07,721 --> 00:52:10,801
- 大人, 我可以说吗  - 直说
- Lord, may I speak? - Freely.

688
00:52:10,961 --> 00:52:13,681
乌巴和他的军队从爱尔兰回来了
Ubba and his army have returned from Ireland.

689
00:52:13,841 --> 00:52:16,801
他们正在北边的塞文河一带登岸
They are coming ashore north of here at the severn.

690
00:52:17,001 --> 00:52:19,001
我的舰队在哪儿?
And my fleet is where?

691
00:52:19,201 --> 00:52:22,201
几天前已从伦敦出发, 快到了
They left lundene several days ago and are nearly here.

692
00:52:22,361 --> 00:52:25,441
每一艘船都会到, 每一个人都会跟着你
Every last ship will be here. Every man will be with you.

693
00:52:25,641 --> 00:52:27,481
这是好消息
That is good news.

694
00:52:32,601 --> 00:52:34,481
我送你去你们的天堂
I dispatch you to your heaven.

695
00:52:37,921 --> 00:52:40,041
不用谢我
No need to thank me.

696
00:52:56,161 --> 00:52:57,801
神父
Father.

697
00:52:58,961 --> 00:53:01,001
乌巴回来了? 
Ubba has returned?

698
00:53:01,161 --> 00:53:02,881
他们说了吗? 
Did they say?

699
00:53:08,361 --> 00:53:10,961
弟兄们, 休战结束了
Men, the peace is over.

700
00:53:11,121 --> 00:53:13,361
备战! 
Prepare for battle.

701
00:53:21,921 --> 00:53:25,321
把撒克逊人质全部杀掉
The Saxon hostages, kill them all.

702
00:53:27,761 --> 00:53:30,121
- 抓住他! - 抓住他! 
- Catch him! - Get him.

703
00:53:30,561 --> 00:53:32,881
把他剁碎! 
Cut him to pieces!

704
00:53:35,241 --> 00:53:37,241
杀了他! 
Kill him!

705
00:53:54,641 --> 00:53:56,041
放他走
Leave him.

706
00:53:56,241 --> 00:53:58,761
我说放他走! 
I say leave him!

707
00:53:59,641 --> 00:54:01,321
拉格纳
Ragnar.

708
00:54:02,281 --> 00:54:05,001
请让开
Please step aside.

709
00:54:05,881 --> 00:54:08,001
你知道所有人质都得死
You know all of the hostages have to die.

710
00:54:09,001 --> 00:54:10,521
那就杀了他
Then kill him.

711
00:54:10,681 --> 00:54:13,721
你尽管去杀他, 但你得先杀了我
You're welcome to kill him. But you have to kill me first.

712
00:54:14,121 --> 00:54:16,321
没有这件事的话我会很开心的
I could happily manage without this.

713
00:54:17,801 --> 00:54:21,561
他是撒克逊人, 是叛徒, 是敌人
He's a Saxon. He's a traitor. He's an enemy.

714
00:54:22,241 --> 00:54:24,681
那你要过去, 就得先杀了我
Well, to get to him, you have to kill me.

715
00:54:26,481 --> 00:54:29,641
我的手下不会跟着你走
My men, they will not follow you.

716
00:54:41,321 --> 00:54:43,881
我最后再给你一次机会
I will give you one last charity.

717
00:54:45,041 --> 00:54:47,401
放他走, 不给马
Release him without a horse.

718
00:54:57,961 --> 00:54:59,801
你没事吧? 
Are you all right?

719
00:55:00,761 --> 00:55:02,321
我不知道说什么好
I have no words.

720
00:55:02,521 --> 00:55:05,361
你走吧, 去看看你的孩子, 去
You should go. Go and see your child. Go.

721
00:55:08,921 --> 00:55:10,441
好
Yes.

722
00:55:10,841 --> 00:55:12,721
我会找到你的
I'll be with you.

723
00:55:14,161 --> 00:55:15,961
你们两个都是
Both of you.

724
00:55:15,985 --> 00:55:17,985

